-- CIBC Hires Craig Wilson to Head North American High-Yield Trading Business
-- B y   D o u g   A l e x a n d e r
-- 2010-09-24T14:01:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-24/cibc-hires-craig-wilson-to-head-north-american-high-yield-trading-business.html
Canadian Imperial Bank of Commerce 
hired  Craig Wilson  from Scotia Capital as head of North American
high-yield trading to expand its debt-capital markets business.  Wilson will join CIBC on Sept. 27 as a managing director,
the Toronto-based bank said today in an internal memo obtained
by Bloomberg News and confirmed by CIBC spokesman  Tom Wallis .  Wilson has 14 years of high-yield market experience in
Toronto and New York as an analyst and trader, according to the
memo. He spent the last two years as a managing director in
fixed income with  Scotia Capital  in Toronto, where he helped set
up the firm’s Canadian high-yield trading platform. He was head
of Scotia Capital’s high-yield research in New York from 2004
until 2008.  Canadian Imperial  is the country’s fifth-biggest
bank.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Alec McCabe at 
 amccabe@bloomberg.net  